{{Infobox hiking trail | name = Haifa Wadis Trail | photo = British building in Ahuza wadi in Haifa.JPG | photo_size = 250px | caption = Haifa Wadis Trail marker | location = Haifa | designation = | established = 2014 | length = {{convert|50|km|mi}} | trailheads = | use = Hiking | elev_gain_and_loss = | elev_change = | lowest = | grade = | difficulty = | season = | months = | sights = | hazards = | surface = | webpage = https://www.facebook.com/WadisTrail }} The '''Haifa Wadis Trail''', ({{lang-he|שביל ואדיות חיפה}}, ''Shvil Vadiot Haifa'') is a hiking path that extends the [[Israel National Trail]] into [[Haifa]]. This [[trail]] that was formed and maintained by Yarok Balev NGO<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yarokbalev.org/en/about/ |title=About the creation of Haifa Wadis Trail |publisher=Yarok Balev NGO |date=2018-04-11 |accessdate=2018-04-11}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=22hqr2-uf0E |title=Students documentary about Haifa Wadis Trail and Yarok Balev NGO |publisher=Gordon College of Haifa |date=2016-07-07 |accessdate=2018-04-11}}</ref> forms a complete hiking circuit of approximately {{convert|50|km|mi}} through the [[wadi]]s of [[Mount Carmel]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/WadisTrail |title=Haifa Wadis Trail |publisher=Haifa Wadis Trail |date=2014-04-17 |accessdate=2014-05-08}}</ref>
The trail is partially marked, and it takes an average of 3 days to hike it as a whole. It has been opened to the public since April 2014,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.teva.org.il/?CategoryID=1073&ArticleID=20383 |title=מסע חלוצי בשביל ואדיות חיפה |publisher=[[Society for the Protection of Nature in Israel]] |date=2014-04-21 |accessdate=2014-05-08}}</ref> and was officially launched on March 2015 after actually marking it.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://app.box.com/s/qtjf18o523uuyi41ey98i78izdkwvpeb |title=שביל ואדיות חיפה הושק במירוץ של 50 ק"מ |publisher=חדשות חיפה והצפון |date=2015-03-11 |accessdate=2018-04-11}}</ref>
The trail passes along cultural and historical landmarks and through national parks around Haifa. It passes near the [[Arc (Bahá'í)|Bahá'í Gardens]], [[Mahmood Mosque, Haifa|Mahmood Mosque]] in [[Kababir]], [[Cave of Elijah|Elijah's Cave]], [[Carmelites]] ruins, [[Technion]] and numerous other sites.<ref>{{cite web|url=link|title=reference_title|publisher=publisher_name|date=2014-04-17|accessdate=2014-05-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yarokbalev.org/en/map/ |title=Haifa Wadis Trail's official map |publisher=Yarok Balev NGO |date=2018-04-11 |accessdate=2018-04-11}}</ref>
==See also== *[[Tourism in Israel]] *[[Geography of Israel]] *[[List of long-distance footpaths]] *[[Wildlife in Israel]]
